\title{CellDeathAnalysis: Comprehensive Analysis of Cell Death Pathways in Gene Expression Data}
\description{
A comprehensive R package for analyzing cell death pathway-related gene expression in transcriptomic data. The package provides curated gene sets for 14 types of regulated cell death (including ferroptosis, cuproptosis, disulfidptosis, pyroptosis, necroptosis, apoptosis, autophagy, and more), pathway scoring methods (ssGSEA, GSVA, AUCell), differential expression analysis, enrichment analysis (ORA and GSEA), survival analysis (Kaplan-Meier, Cox regression, time-dependent ROC), single-cell analysis, machine learning prediction models, interactive Shiny application, and publication-ready visualizations. Ideal for cancer research, immunology, and cell biology studies.
